cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.DB. 

The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) protocols for distributed storage systems (DSSs) using linear codes. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the fundamental limits of information transmission and storage. The paper also involves the design and analysis of algorithms for PIR, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the security aspects of PIR, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper extensively uses coding theory, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DB (Databases).
